<paragraph id="F51D2474FFB4FF82FF47FDB8FA83FD03" blockId="6.[136,1452,158,1229]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">
<emphasis id="C7D6F866FFB4FF82FF47FDB8FED1FDF7" bold="true" box="[189,265,518,544]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Notes:</emphasis>
—During the expedition to 
<collectingCountry id="8DB564E4FFB4FF82FDCDFDB8FD4EFDF7" box="[567,662,518,544]" name="Vietnam" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
in 2016, 
<specimenCount id="E3A4EFFDFFB4FF82FD00FDB9FC49FDF7" box="[762,913,518,545]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
of a presumably unknown species was collected. 
<collectorName id="585741A2FFB4FF82FF72FD94FF2EFD93" box="[136,246,554,580]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Thorough</collectorName>
morphological and molecular study has shown its uniqueness and independent taxonomic status (
<bibRefCitation id="91335985FFB4FF82FAD5FD94FEDAFDBF" author="Malysheva, E. &amp; Malysheva, V. &amp; Alexandrova, A. &amp; Morozova, O." pageId="6" pageNumber="284" pagination="233 - 254" refId="ref6958" refString="Malysheva, E., Malysheva, V., Alexandrova, A. &amp; Morozova, O. (2019) Observations on Pluteaceae in Vietnam. 1. New species and new records of Volvariella. Phytotaxa 408 (4): 233 - 254. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 408.4.1" type="journal article" year="2019">
Malysheva 
<emphasis id="C7D6F866FFB4FF82FF72FDF1FF67FDBF" box="[136,191,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<collectorName id="585741A2FFB4FF82FEE9FDF1FEA3FDBE" box="[275,379,591,617]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">However</collectorName>
, this specimen was immature, and then we could not study in detail the features of basidiospores. 
<collectorName id="585741A2FFB4FF82FF72FDCCFF3CFD5B" box="[136,228,626,652]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Another</collectorName>
collection, found by one of the co-authors (
<collectorName id="585741A2FFB4FF82FD21FDCCFC9DFD5A" box="[731,837,626,653]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">E. Popov</collectorName>
) in 
<collectingRegion id="3766EA96FFB4FF82FC89FDCCFB9BFD5B" box="[883,1091,626,652]" country="Vietnam" name="Nghe An" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Nghe An province</collectingRegion>
of 
<collectingCountry id="8DB564E4FFB4FF82FB91FDCCFB12FD5B" box="[1131,1226,626,652]" name="Vietnam" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
in 2019, turned out to be identical to the previous one. 
<collectorName id="585741A2FFB4FF82FDEAFD28FD9AFD67" box="[528,578,662,688]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">This</collectorName>
made it possible to clarify the lacking morphological characteristics. 
<collectorName id="585741A2FFB4FF82FAB7FD29FA5BFD66" box="[1357,1411,663,689]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Here</collectorName>
we describe a new species, providing an amended and combined description based on the two studied collections.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F51D2474FFB4FF82FF47FD60FD6FFC23" blockId="6.[136,1452,158,1229]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">
The macroscopic characteristics of our collections mostly agree with the description of 
<taxonomicName id="32A25FF7FFB4FF82FB68FD60FA57FD2F" authorityName="Singer" authorityYear="1949" baseAuthorityName="Schaeffer" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[1170,1423,734,760]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="bombycina">
<emphasis id="C7D6F866FFB4FF82FB68FD60FA57FD2F" box="[1170,1423,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Volvariella bombycina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in terms of stout basidiocarps with light-coloured pale brownish and entirely squamulose pileus, thick stipe, and spacious brown volva. At the same time, the microscopic characters, such as the size of basidiospores and the peculiar form of cheilocystidia with the apical papilla, make it close to 
<taxonomicName id="32A25FF7FFB4FF82FD03FCF5FCA2FCB3" authorityName="Singer" authorityYear="1949" baseAuthorityName="Bulliard" baseAuthorityYear="1786" box="[761,890,842,868]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="volvacea">
<emphasis id="C7D6F866FFB4FF82FD03FCF5FCA2FCB3" box="[761,890,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">V. volvacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="32A25FF7FFB4FF82FC70FCF4FBA1FCB3" authorityName="E. F. Malysheva, E. S. Popov &amp; A. V. Alexandrova" authorityYear="2022" box="[906,1145,842,868]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="C7D6F866FFB4FF82FC70FCF4FBA1FCB3" box="[906,1145,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Volvariella orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="32A25FF7FFB4FF82FAE9FCF5FA73FCB3" authorityName="Singer" authorityYear="1949" baseAuthorityName="Schaeffer" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[1299,1451,842,868]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="bombycina">
<emphasis id="C7D6F866FFB4FF82FAE9FCF5FA73FCB3" box="[1299,1451,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">V. bombycina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in velvety outer surface of volva and broader hymenial cystidia with subcapitate apex, and it mainly differs from 
<taxonomicName id="32A25FF7FFB4FF82FA6DFCD1FF34FC7B" authorityName="Singer" authorityYear="1949" baseAuthorityName="Bulliard" baseAuthorityYear="1786" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="volvacea">
<emphasis id="C7D6F866FFB4FF82FA6DFCD1FF34FC7B" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">V. volvacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in pilose-squamulose pileus, ochre brown or olive brown volva and the presence of caulocystidia (
<bibRefCitation id="91335985FFB4FF82FAC4FC2CFF19FC07" author="Boekhout, T." pageId="6" pageNumber="284" pagination="56 - 64" refId="ref4422" refString="Boekhout, T. (1990) Volvariella. In: Bas, C., Kuyper, Th. W., Noordeloos, M. E. &amp; Vellinga, E. C. (Eds.) Flora Agaricina Neerlandica 2. A. A. Balkema, Rotterdam, pp. 56 - 64." type="book chapter" year="1990">Boekhout 1990</bibRefCitation>
). Moreover, the phylogenetic analyses of the combined nrITS and nrLSU sequences demonstrate the independent position of these three species on the tree (
<figureCitation id="6D9938F1FFB4FF82FD9FFC64FD7EFC23" box="[613,678,986,1012]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1842,1864]" captionTargetBox="[152,1388,203,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-24@3.[151,1436,190,1818]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1.—Best tree from the ML analysis of the nrITS-nrLSU dataset for Volvariella species, with Cantharocybe gruberi as outgroup. Bootstrap support values and Posterior probability (BS/PP) are given above the branches.All tips are labelled with taxon name and voucher or strain numbers. For taxon in bold the sequences are generated in present study." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541460" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6541460/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F51D2474FFB4FF82FF47FC40FB7FFB1A" blockId="6.[136,1452,158,1229]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">
The macromorphology of 
<taxonomicName id="32A25FF7FFB4FF82FE25FC41FDBCFBCF" authorityName="E. F. Malysheva, E. S. Popov &amp; A. V. Alexandrova" authorityYear="2022" box="[479,612,1022,1048]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="C7D6F866FFB4FF82FE25FC41FDBCFBCF" box="[479,612,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">V. orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
makes it also close to 
<taxonomicName id="32A25FF7FFB4FF82FCADFC41FF65FBEB" authority="(Berk. &amp; Broome 1871: 151) Singer (1949: 401)" authorityName="Singer" authorityPageNumber="401" authorityYear="1949" baseAuthorityName="Berk. &amp; Broome" baseAuthorityPageNumber="151" baseAuthorityYear="1871" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="diplasia">
<emphasis id="C7D6F866FFB4FF82FCADFC41FC12FBCF" box="[855,970,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">V. diplasia</emphasis>
(Berk. &amp; Broome 1871: 151) 
<bibRefCitation id="91335985FFB4FF82FAEEFC40FF65FBEB" author="Singer, R." pageId="6" pageNumber="284" pagination="1 - 832" refId="ref7787" refString="Singer, R. (1949) The Agaricales in modern taxonomy. Lilloa 22: 1 - 832." type="journal article" year="1949">Singer (1949: 401)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, edible mushroom species currently cultivated in both tropical and subtropical regions. The main differences between the two species are colour of the volva, shape and size of basidiospores and cheilocystidia. The volva of 
<taxonomicName id="32A25FF7FFB4FF82FF72FBD5FF27FB53" authorityName="Singer" authorityYear="1949" baseAuthorityName="Berk. &amp; Broome" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[136,255,1130,1156]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="diplasia">
<emphasis id="C7D6F866FFB4FF82FF72FBD5FF27FB53" box="[136,255,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">V. diplasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more light coloured, while 
<taxonomicName id="32A25FF7FFB4FF82FDA6FBD5FD3CFB53" authorityName="E. F. Malysheva, E. S. Popov &amp; A. V. Alexandrova" authorityYear="2022" box="[604,740,1130,1156]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="C7D6F866FFB4FF82FDA6FBD5FD3CFB53" box="[604,740,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">V. orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has dark brown volva with distinct olive tint; the spores of 
<taxonomicName id="32A25FF7FFB4FF82FA6DFBD5FF3AFB7F" authorityName="Singer" authorityYear="1949" baseAuthorityName="Berk. &amp; Broome" baseAuthorityYear="1871" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="diplasia">
<emphasis id="C7D6F866FFB4FF82FA6DFBD5FF3AFB7F" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">V. diplasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are more elongate, often subcylindrical and frequently 10 µm or longer, and cheilocystidia are piriform or clavate and significantly smaller (33–50 × 18–26 µm) (Pegler 1987) than ones in 
<taxonomicName id="32A25FF7FFB4FF82FBE3FB0DFB47FB1B" authorityName="E. F. Malysheva, E. S. Popov &amp; A. V. Alexandrova" authorityYear="2022" box="[1049,1183,1202,1228]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="C7D6F866FFB4FF82FBE3FB0DFB47FB1B" box="[1049,1183,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">V. orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
